The answer to that question is Nvidia (NASDAQ: NVDA), even though the stock has already climbed 800% over the past three years.  Nvidia has played a key role since the first days of the AI boom, and this is because it designs the crucial element that makes AI work: chips.

headline: Nvidia insiders cash out $1 billion worth of shares
summary:
Nvidia insiders have sold more than $1 billion of the company’s stock over the past 12 months including a recent surge in trading as they cash in on investors’ enthusiasm for artificial intelligence. 
More than $500 million of the share sales took place this month as the California-based chips designer’s share price climbed to a record high. 
Investors have piled back into the stock, making it the world’s most valuable company as they bet on huge demand for chips to power AI applications. The price rise comes after a turbulent year in which Nvidia was knocked by US-China trade tensions and Chinese AI breakthroughs that threatened demand for its products.
